These wrap the separately-installed, independently-licensed `zairachem`
CLI (Ersilia Open Source Initiative -- see
https://github.com/ersilia-os/zaira-chem for its own license terms,
which are NOT superseded or altered by qFoldIT's Apache-2.0 wrapper
code calling it as an external subprocess). Ersilia's main model-hub
repository is GPL-3.0-licensed; zaira-chem's own LICENSE file was not
directly inspected during this addition, so don't assume it's
necessarily the same terms without checking. ZairaChem itself is not
vendored or redistributed by this repository -- confirmed real CLI
flags used here (`fit -i ... -m ...`, `predict -i ... -m ... -o ...`)
match Ersilia's own published usage examples.

